&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;In Ukraine, a metropolitan of the UOC was sentenced in absentia to 11 years for collaboration and support for the annexation.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 18, the Desnyansky District Court of Chernihiv sentenced Metropolitan Panteleimon (Povoroznyuk) of Luhansk and Alchevsk in absentia to 11 years in prison. He was also deprived of the right to hold any positions in religious organizations for 13 years, and all his property is subject to confiscation. This is &lt;a href=&quot;https://risu.ua/mitropolita-upc-mp-zasudzheno-za-kolaboracijnu-diyalnist-na-okupovanih-teritoriyah_n157057&quot;&gt;reported&lt;/a&gt; by the Religious Information Service of Ukraine with &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/shumylo/posts/pfbid0QDbdYhZGBTV1BNC3nzF4amG1YTmUwQbiZusaxuvFFmAQEqBBm1KmLVK2DDBXWzpFl&quot;&gt;a link&lt;/a&gt; to Serhiy Shumylo, who published the court&#x27;s verdict.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Panteleimon is the head of the Synodal Department of the UOC for Family Affairs. He was found guilty of collaborationist activities in the occupied territories, public support for Russian aggression, and participation in the Kremlin&#x27;s &quot;meeting&quot; on September 30, 2022, where &quot;agreements&quot; on the accession of the captured Ukrainian regions to the Russian Federation were signed. At that event, the bishop was present in vestments, representing the UOC and, according to the court&#x27;s wording, his presence &quot;non-verbally supported&quot; the actions of the occupiers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The court examined publications in the media, witness testimonies, and also pointed to Panteleimon&#x27;s systemic cooperation with the occupation structures. His property was seized in the Luhansk, Kyiv, and Vinnytsia regions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As the publication notes, despite repeated appeals by clergy and laity, the UOC Synod has not yet suspended the metropolitan from his duties and has not applied canonical sanctions to him.&lt;/p&gt;

