&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;In churches and cathedrals of Belarus, they prayed for the word banned in Russia.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 22, in Belarus, by order of the authorities, the All-Belarusian Prayer for Peace was heard. As &lt;a href=&quot;https://belta.by/society/view/vsebelorusskaja-molitva-za-mir-prozvuchit-22-ijunja-vo-vseh-hramah-belarusi-721679-2025/&quot;&gt;stated&lt;/a&gt; by the Commissioner for Religious and Ethnic Affairs &lt;b&gt;Aleksandr Rumak&lt;/b&gt;, it was supposed to be prayed in all the temples of the Belarusian Orthodox Church and the Roman Catholic churches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to him, the prayer is a reminder to the current generations of the value of peace and well-being in homes, emphasized the Commissioner for Religious and Ethnic Affairs.&lt;/p&gt;

