&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Russian Pentecostals discussed how to help the occupiers&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 10 in St. Petersburg, an interfaith scientific and practical conference &quot;Fundamentals of Assistance to Combatants and Their Families: Psychological and Spiritual Aspects of Resocialization. The Role of Denominations&quot; was held.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The conference was organized by the &quot;Prayer Breakfast&quot; Foundation with the support of the city authorities and traditional confessions of St. Petersburg.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More than 20 ministers of the Pentecostal church &quot;Mission &#x27;Good News&#x27;&quot;, many of whom are professional psychologists and teachers who already work with veterans, took part in the event.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&quot;The main theme of the event is how to unite the efforts of the state, religious organizations and specialists to support the combatants&quot;&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

#Russia #Pentecostals

