&lt;b&gt;&quot;To bring love where hatred reigns&quot; — a sermon by the anti-war priest Georgy Martyshevsky&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;It has become more convenient for a person to kill — that&#x27;s all the progress.&quot; This is how the Sunday sermon of Belarusian archpriest Georgy Martyshevsky, published on the YouTube channel of Novaya Gazeta, begins. It is about those who remain faithful to the Gospel in the face of violence and destruction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Father Georgy is a priest from Belarus. Due to persecution, he was forced to leave the country and today continues his ministry in Italy. His message sounds simple: everyone can turn the tide for the better if they bring love and peace to the world instead of hatred and war.&lt;/p&gt;

