&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Mikhail Burmistrov on the &quot;Night Aronych&quot; channel: why the Russian Orthodox Church accepted the war.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A new episode of a conversation with Mikhail Burmistrov - a philosopher, theologian, and thinker - has been released on the YouTube channel &quot;Night Aronych&quot;. This is a continuation of a series in which the author offers a deep analysis of the war from the perspective of church ideology.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The main topic is why the Russian Orthodox Church has almost entirely accepted the war. Burmistrov examines how this happened and what ideas underlie it: from the myth of the &quot;holy war&quot; and the &quot;Russian world&quot; to the theological justification of murder as &quot;God&#x27;s permission&quot; and &quot;invisible warfare&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#russia #roc&lt;/p&gt;

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Alaudinov is now a friend, not an enemy, for the &quot;Forty Forties&quot;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The meeting of the core activists of the Orthodox movement &quot;Forty Forties&quot; with the Chechen general &lt;b&gt;Apti Alaudinov&lt;/b&gt;, who had called the Orthodox schema-hegumen &quot;a moron in a cassock&quot;, lasted 8.5 hours.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Initially, we wanted to demand public apologies from the general, but after the conversation, we realized that this was not necessary. It was enough for us that the general admitted that he was wrong in his name-calling against Father Gavriil, that he did not know who it was when he recorded the video in a fit of emotion, and that he was deeply hurt by that very episode from the schema-hegumen&#x27;s sermon, where he spoke disparagingly of Islam and Muslims in Moscow, generalizing everyone. ... We talked a lot with the general about the past, present and future, about the challenges facing Russia. We talked about demography, Russophobia, Checheno-phobia. ... In general, we realized one thing - Apti Alaudinov is not an enemy of Russians and Orthodox, but a friend,&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/kormukhin/1547&quot;&gt;said&lt;/a&gt; the leader of the &quot;Forty Forties&quot; &lt;b&gt;Andrey Kormukhin&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

#Russia #Orthodox #Muslims

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&quot;By the Grace of God&quot; representatives of the Russian Orthodox Church were awarded for assistance to the front&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Archimandrite &lt;b&gt;Mikhail (Semenov)&lt;/b&gt;, the abbot of the Monastery of the Savior Not Made by Hands in the village of Klykovo, Kozelsk Diocese of the Russian Orthodox Church, &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/vestnik_2022/38053&quot;&gt;reported&lt;/a&gt; that he and the deacon were awarded medals &quot;For Assistance to the Front&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&quot;By the Grace of God, by order of the Commander of Military Unit 38838, number 777, the residents of the male Monastery of the Savior Not Made by Hands, Archimandrite Mikhail (Semenov) and Deacon Evgeny Vasilyev, were awarded,&quot;&lt;/i&gt; he reported.&lt;/p&gt;

#Russia #Orthodox #ROC

