&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The movement &quot;AllatRa&quot; has been recognized as extremist in Russia.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 24, 2025, the Supreme Court of Russia granted the claim of the Prosecutor General&#x27;s Office to recognize the international public movement &quot;AllatRa&quot; as extremist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The movement was created in the early 2010s in Kyiv. The doctrine is compiled from various historical, philosophical, mythological, religious and esoteric ideas, spiritual practices, the author&#x27;s interpretation of the idea of the animal and spiritual principle in a person and the reincarnation of the soul. At the same time, conspiracy theories play a notable role in the ideology of the movement, in particular, the idea of the need to fight against global Zionism, Stalinism and the messianic idea that the Russian nation is called to save humanity and unite the peoples of the world around itself. The idea of the fateful role of the &quot;Russian world&quot; for humanity is combined by the ideologists of the &quot;AllatRa&quot; movement with a negative perception of power as a source of repression, the injustice of laws, and the logical conditionality of mass protests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 2023, the Prosecutor General&#x27;s Office of the Russian Federation declared the activities of the International Public Movement &quot;ALLATRA&quot;, based in Ukraine, as undesirable in Russia, since its activists &quot;receive instructions from Ukrainian curators about the need to establish contacts with representatives of opposition forces and conduct coordinated actions to discredit the policies of federal and regional authorities,&quot; including the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the same year, the Security Service of Ukraine announced the neutralization of the &quot;international criminal organization AllatRa&quot;. &quot;Under the guise of &#x27;missionary work&#x27;, the participants of the religious sect justified Russia&#x27;s armed aggression and publicly promoted the Kremlin&#x27;s idea of creating a &#x27;union of Slavic peoples&#x27; under the leadership of Moscow,&quot; the SBU said.&lt;/p&gt;

#россия #культы

