&lt;b&gt;Russian Christians and opposition members appealed to the German Chancellor to protect political prisoners&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Archpriest &lt;b&gt;Andrey Kordochkin&lt;/b&gt; and priest &lt;b&gt;Valerian Dunin-Barkovskiy&lt;/b&gt;, founders of the project to assist anti-war priests, initiated an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=9994973037250448&amp;amp;id=100002135538319&amp;amp;mibextid=wwXIfr&amp;amp;rdid=6zlYKdcxn67lzvhB&quot;&gt;appeal&lt;/a&gt; to the Chancellor of Germany, &lt;b&gt;Friedrich Merz&lt;/b&gt;, requesting assistance in the release of political prisoners in Russia.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The signatories of the letter are Russian emigrants in Germany, including &lt;b&gt;Ilya Yashin&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;Andrey Pivovarov&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;Kevin Lik&lt;/b&gt; (released in 2024 as a result of an exchange), human rights activist &lt;b&gt;Olga Romanova&lt;/b&gt;, critic &lt;b&gt;Anna Narinskaya&lt;/b&gt;, gallery owner &lt;b&gt;Marat Gelman&lt;/b&gt;, and others.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The authors &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dw.com/ru/oppozicia-rf-prosit-kanclera-frg-pomoc-osvobodit-politzaklucennyh/a-73038445&quot;&gt;indicate&lt;/a&gt; that more than a thousand political prisoners remain in Russian prisons, including the elderly and severely ill. Many are subjected to torture, including legalized forms, such as being held in inhumane conditions in solitary confinement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The appeal states:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;We recognize in modern Russia the main features of the fascist political architecture. The denial of personal rights and freedoms, the cult of war and heroic death, the militarization of religion, the criminal prosecution of LGBTQ+ and Jehovah&#x27;s Witnesses - all this revives the darkest pages of Germany&#x27;s history in the 20th century. The Ukrainian people are denied the right to their own existence.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The signatories believe that a possible solution could be an exchange or mutual amnesty: this would give a chance for freedom to both supporters of the &quot;Russian world&quot; in Ukraine and Russian political prisoners.&lt;/p&gt;

