&lt;b&gt;Archbishop Ignazio Cefaliá has arrived in Belarus as the new Apostolic Nuncio&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 26, in Minsk, the first official meeting of the Catholic bishops of Belarus with the new Apostolic Nuncio, Archbishop Ignazio Cefaliá, took place. This was &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.instagram.com/p/DLYKx_JMvE0/?img_index=1&quot;&gt;reported&lt;/a&gt; by the Diocese of Pinsk, which published a photo of the meeting on its Instagram account (and this was &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/katolik_life/1949&quot;&gt;noted&lt;/a&gt; by the Katolik.life publication).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;During the visit, the diplomatic representative of the Pope handed the bishops a document from the Apostolic See about his appointment. The meeting took place at the residence of Archbishop Józef Stanewski, who invited the guests to lunch. Each of the hierarchs had the opportunity to personally communicate with the new nuncio and tell about their experience of service.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The arrival of Archbishop Cefaliá raises special hopes among the faithful - including his participation in the main Mass at the festival in Budslau and possible assistance in the release of imprisoned priests.&lt;/p&gt;

