&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;A Jehovah&#x27;s Witness with a disability was sent to a penal colony for talking about religion&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 23, the Cherkessk City Court &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sova-center.ru/misuse/news/persecution/2024/03/d49547/&quot;&gt;found&lt;/a&gt; 45-year-old Jehovah&#x27;s Witness &lt;b&gt;Vladimir Fomin&lt;/b&gt; guilty under Parts 1.1 and 2 of Article 282.2 of the Criminal Code (involvement in the activities of an extremist organization and participation in it) and sentenced him to 4.5 years in a general regime colony.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On February 21, 2024, a search was conducted at the home of Fomin and his wife. On March 21, the believer was detained, and two days later the Cherkessk City Court sent him to a pre-trial detention center. Fomin became disabled at the age of 20 when he was beaten on the doorstep on the territory of a house of worship by young people hostile to Jehovah&#x27;s Witnesses. In the pre-trial detention center, his condition worsened, and he lost consciousness during one of the court hearings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason for the criminal prosecution of the Jehovah&#x27;s Witness was, in particular, the fact that he conducted conversations on religious topics with other people.&lt;/p&gt;

