&lt;p&gt;The Deputy Head of the Main Military-Political Directorate of the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation, &lt;b&gt;Apti Alaudinov&lt;/b&gt;, published &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/AptiAlaudinovAKHMAT/11702&quot;&gt;a video&lt;/a&gt; from the &quot;Akhmat&quot; unit, in which Orthodox priests and a Muslim imam together with soldiers chant &quot;Akhmat is power&quot;, &quot;God is one&quot;, &quot;Allahu Akbar&quot; and &quot;Christ is risen - truly risen&quot;. The military are holding a flag with the image of an Orthodox cross and a Muslim crescent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to Alaudinov, &quot;representatives of traditional faiths&quot; provide soldiers with &quot;spiritual support&quot;, and the SVO itself is a &quot;struggle against the forces of evil&quot;. &quot;We are fighting side by side against the army of the Antichrist!&quot; - he said, apparently referring to the Ukrainian army.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The demonstrative religious unity in the Russian army is increasingly being used to legitimize the war as &quot;sacred&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

#russia #orthodox #muslims

