&lt;b&gt;Expert of the Ukrainian State Service for Ethnopolitics: The ban on the UOC violates international law&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hzqwNV_ANaU&quot;&gt;interview&lt;/a&gt; with the publication &quot;Viche&quot;, which was &lt;a href=&quot;https://spzh.eu/ru/news/86970-ekspert-hess-zapret-upts-protivorechit-mezhdunarodnomu-pravu&quot;&gt;noted&lt;/a&gt; by the publication of the Union of Orthodox Journalists, lawyer &lt;b&gt;Dmitry Vovk&lt;/b&gt; - an expert of the State Service of Ukraine for Ethnopolitics and Conscience (GESS) - stated that the ban on the UOC based solely on its canonical connection with the ROC contradicts international law.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The state must prove administrative subordination - receiving instructions from the ROC and their implementation,&quot; he explained. Otherwise, there are no grounds for the ban.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Vovk emphasized that international norms require applying the ban as a last resort and only in the case of illegal actions in which the entire organization or its leadership is involved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The cancellation of registration hits not the hierarchs, but the ordinary believers. The state is obliged to first use less stringent measures,&quot; the expert added.&lt;/p&gt;

#ukraine #uoc

