&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Who is this patron who plays Woland right in Belarusian churches and then gifts them with relics?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A festival with pro-Kremlin rock groups, carriages and knights, &quot;rarest relics&quot; in a church — all this is organized and financed by sanctioned businessmen.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One of them is &lt;b&gt;Oleg Orlov&lt;/b&gt;, a former parliamentary candidate, an esotericist and an artist who shoots music videos in churches in the image of Woland and with the &quot;living doll&quot; Margo.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Orlov claims that he personally helped the churches in Pruzhany, Ruzhany and Stolbtsy, transferred reliquaries and icons. But his views are a mix of the Bible, Castaneda, Roerich and Blavatsky, and he himself talks about &quot;summoning spirits&quot; and the &quot;great Nothingness&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have collected all that is known about businessman Orlov and his strange connections with churches in our &lt;a href=&quot;https://belarus2020.churchby.info/orloff/&quot;&gt;investigation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

