&lt;p&gt;On the day of remembrance of the saints of St. Petersburg, the anti-war archpriest Andrey Kordochkin reflects on his native city and its righteous ones. In his sermon, he speaks of Blessed Xenia, who wore men&#x27;s clothing and a man&#x27;s name, and of the priest John of Kronstadt, who was not accepted by his colleagues - and wonders: how would they be received in today&#x27;s Russia?&lt;/p&gt;

