&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&quot;Save Nobel&#x27;s life&quot;: Venclova calls on the Pope of Rome&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Human rights defender and former political prisoner &lt;b&gt;Leonid Sudalenko&lt;/b&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/leonid.sudalenko.7/posts/pfbid02Zb2jGJcei9SgWJkYxQ8uXQzkuCsgcnP4ZD9NTQiHTurrybjktDGomdEMBDjT7hRzl&quot;&gt;reported&lt;/a&gt; about the appeal of Lithuanian poet and Soviet dissident &lt;b&gt;Tomas Venclova&lt;/b&gt; to Pope &lt;b&gt;Leo XIV&lt;/b&gt; to intervene and demand the release of &lt;b&gt;Ales Bialiatski&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nobel Peace Prize laureate, Catholic and human rights defender Ales Bialiatski is serving 10 years of imprisonment in harsh conditions, without medical assistance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sudalenko emphasized that it is the moral authority of the Vatican that can save Bialiatski&#x27;s life - the only Nobel laureate currently imprisoned. He also recalled that Pope &lt;b&gt;Benedict XVI&lt;/b&gt; had previously expressed support for Ales.&lt;/p&gt;

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision&quot;&gt;Christian Vision: NO TO WAR!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pope Leo XIV — To Ukraine: I share your pain&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pope &lt;b&gt;Leo XIV&lt;/b&gt; expressed solidarity with Ukrainians suffering from the consequences of the war. &quot;I share your pain for the prisoners and victims of this senseless war,&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://x.com/Pontifex/status/1938939496076067171&quot;&gt;he wrote&lt;/a&gt; on June 28 on the social network X, stressing that the faith of the Ukrainian people is now undergoing a severe test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;President &lt;b&gt;Volodymyr Zelenskyy&lt;/b&gt; responded to the Pope&#x27;s message, thanking him for his constant prayers and sympathy. According to the head of state, a just peace is possible only through joint efforts to stop Russian aggression.&lt;/p&gt;

#vatican #pope #ukraine

