&lt;b&gt;The Vitebsk Diocese collected items for the Talaya Foundation, which is engaged in evacuating children from Ukraine&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the request of the Alexei Talaya Charitable Foundation, the parishes of the Vitebsk Diocese organized a &lt;a href=&quot;https://vitprav.by/60568.html&quot;&gt;collection of bedding&lt;/a&gt; &quot;for those affected in the frontline areas&quot;. Parishioners and students of the Vitebsk Theological Seminary sorted the collected items and handed them over to the representative of the Foundation in the Vitebsk region, &lt;b&gt;Lidiya Shishko&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Once again, we express our deepest gratitude and sincere gratitude to all the parishioners who took part in this noble cause. Only through joint efforts can we provide assistance to those affected and at least alleviate their difficult fate,&quot; the representatives of the Talaya Foundation thanked the believers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Alexei Talaya&lt;/b&gt; is a Belarusian Paralympian and pro-government activist who is also known for his activities in &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dw.com/ru/rassledovanie-zurnalistov-kto-sponsiruet-vyvoz-ukrainskih-detej-v-belarus/a-66409353&quot;&gt;organizing the evacuation&lt;/a&gt; of Ukrainian children to Belarus. The athlete emphasizes that his organization acts only for humanitarian purposes, but there is an assumption that assistance is also provided to the Russian army.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Last year, Talaya&#x27;s associate, the activist of the Foundation &lt;b&gt;Yevgeny Nazarevich&lt;/b&gt;, who is engaged in the delivery of humanitarian aid from Belarus to the occupied territories of Ukraine, reported about the certificate he received for &lt;a href=&quot;https://nashaniva.com/amp/ru/352008&quot;&gt;supporting&lt;/a&gt; the Russian army and contributing to the &quot;common victory&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Activists of the Talaya Foundation run a &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/belarus_donbassu&quot;&gt;Telegram channel &quot;Belarus with Donbass&quot;&lt;/a&gt;, which publishes posts with pro-Russian propaganda between information about the provided humanitarian aid.&lt;/p&gt;

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision&quot;&gt;Christian Vision: NO TO WAR!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;b&gt;The temple of St. Dimitry of Rostov in Donbass has been destroyed&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a result of Russian shelling, the UOC (Ukrainian Orthodox Church) temple in honor of St. Dimitry of Rostov in the village of Zolotoy Kolodets, Donetsk region, was destroyed. This was reported on June 30, 2025 by the press service of the Pokrovsky Vicariate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The church suffered serious damage - the debris of the structure is scattered throughout the temple territory.&lt;/p&gt;

#ukraine #uoc #destruction

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The head prison priest of the Russian Orthodox Church spoke about how to teach murderers and rapists to fight against Ukraine.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 27, the 10th All-Russian Scientific and Practical Conference &quot;Interaction of the Russian Orthodox Church and the Penal Enforcement System of the Russian Federation&quot; was held at the University of the Federal Penitentiary Service of Russia in St. Petersburg. A round table was held within the framework of the conference, dedicated to the care of suspects, accused and convicted persons who wish to fight and are fighting against Ukraine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;It is not enough just to serve a prayer service for future warriors, it is necessary to necessarily tell them a word about what their inner state should be, from what they should guard themselves spiritually, what they should not allow themselves under any circumstances. After all, how they assimilate these tips and follow them depends on how they return back, how much their psyche will be traumatized there, at war, and how quickly they will recover after returning,&quot; emphasized the chairman of the Synodal Department for Prison Ministry, Priest Kirill Markovsky.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to him, a prisoner mobilized for war &quot;must understand that he is fighting evil, which, if not stopped, will devour many lives. That he fulfills the commandment of Christ &quot;Greater love has no one than this, that someone lay down his life for his friends&quot; (John 15:13). That if he felt a calling from God to go where a fierce struggle with the enemy is going on, he must follow this path without hesitation, remembering that for him this is God&#x27;s blessing.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

#Russia #Orthodox #ROC

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians Against War!&lt;/a&gt;

