&lt;b&gt;Священник РПЦ предложил не накладывать на участников “СВО” жестких епитимий
&lt;/b&gt;
26 июня в Православном Свято-Тихоновском гуманитарном университете РПЦ &lt;a href=&quot;https://priest.today/seminars/66&quot;&gt;состоялся&lt;/a&gt; пастырский семинар по вопросам окормления участников войны против Украины и их семей.

Первая часть семинара была посвящена обсуждению конкретных случаев, связанных с участием воинов в церковных Таинствах. Специалист по каноническому праву, преподаватель ПСТГУ протоиерей &lt;b&gt;Димитрий Пашков&lt;/b&gt; отметил, что правило святителя &lt;b&gt;Василия Великого &lt;/b&gt;об участии в Таинствах воинов, вернувшихся с фронта, подходит к решению этого вопроса очень бережно и индивидуально, не предъявляя жесткой и универсальной нормы: &lt;i&gt;«При всей детальной регламентации епитимий за тяжкие грехи, святитель Василий оставляет воздержание от причастия воинов, участвовавших в сражениях, на их усмотрение».
&lt;/i&gt;
#Россия #православные #рпц

messages.translated_message:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;A priest of the Russian Orthodox Church proposed not to impose harsh penances on the participants of the &quot;special military operation&quot;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 26, at the Orthodox St. Tikhon&#x27;s University of the Humanities of the Russian Orthodox Church, &lt;a href=&quot;https://priest.today/seminars/66&quot;&gt;a pastoral seminar&lt;/a&gt; was held on the issues of caring for the participants of the war against Ukraine and their families.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first part of the seminar was devoted to the discussion of specific cases related to the participation of soldiers in the Church&#x27;s Sacraments. The specialist in canon law, a teacher at St. Tikhon&#x27;s University, Archpriest &lt;b&gt;Dimitry Pashkov&lt;/b&gt;, noted that the rule of St. &lt;b&gt;Basil the Great&lt;/b&gt; on the participation in the Sacraments of soldiers returning from the front, approaches the solution of this issue very carefully and individually, without imposing a rigid and universal norm: &lt;i&gt;&quot;Despite the detailed regulation of penances for grave sins, St. Basil leaves the abstinence from communion of soldiers who have participated in battles, to their own discretion.&quot;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

#Russia #Orthodox #ROC

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians Against War!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;In Russia, a prayer service to a pagan deity will be held for participants in the war against Ukraine&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On July 6, a Tailgan - a prayer service in honor of the great deity &lt;b&gt;Bukhe Baatar&lt;/b&gt; - will be held at the Tengeri Shamanic Center in Ulan-Ude, Russia (Buryatia), including for participants in the war against Ukraine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Bukhe Baatar is the patron of warriors, athletes and law enforcement. Since ancient times, before important competitions and battles, they have turned to him for support, fortitude and blessing. Worship of this great deity is especially significant for the defenders of the Motherland and their families - for today, more than ever, the strength of spirit, courage and valor are important,&quot; the shamanic center said.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#Russia #Pagans&lt;/p&gt;

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Public Chamber of the Russian Federation called to &quot;protect our Muslims&quot; from newcomers.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The chairman of the centralized religious organization &quot;International Islamic Mission&quot;, Shafig Pshikhaсhev, criticized Russians who do not notice Muslims among the participants in the war against Ukraine. &quot;Today, 8,000 ethnic Tajiks are participating in the SVO, but they remember those 19 people who staged a terrorist attack in the &#x27;Crocus&#x27;,&quot; he said during a meeting at the Public Chamber of the Russian Federation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the same time, Pshikhaсhev, &quot;unfortunately, along with migrants, extremism with pseudo-religious slogans is now penetrating into us [Russia. - ed.]&quot;. According to him, a preaching of a return to the origins of Islam is coming from the East, ignoring the traditions of the peoples of Russia in professing their faith, and from the West - &quot;some community of Euro-Muslims&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The chairman of the Commission of the Public Chamber of the Russian Federation on Security and Interaction with the Public Monitoring Commission, Mikhail Anichkin, put forward the slogan: &quot;It&#x27;s time to protect our Muslims!&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Migrants come to us not only without a general education, but even without knowledge of the sacred texts for Muslims. They assimilate quotes from the Quran from the words of preachers who are sometimes extremist. It is necessary to solve the issue with migrants, as in the UAE, where they come only to work, without wives and children. Otherwise, the state should take into account not only their contribution to the economy, but also the costs of social security for their families in Russia,&quot; he said.&lt;/p&gt;

#Russia #Muslims

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;In Russia, the verdict was passed on Vissarion - the leader of the Church of the Last Testament&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 30, the Zheleznodorozhny Court of Novosibirsk &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sova-center.ru/religion/news/harassment/intervention/2025/06/d51824/&quot;&gt;convicted&lt;/a&gt; the leaders of the Church of the Last Testament. The court found &lt;b&gt;Sergey Torop (Vissarion)&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;Vadim Redkin&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;Vladimir Vedernikov&lt;/b&gt; guilty under Part 1 of Article 239 of the Criminal Code (creation of a non-profit organization that encroaches on the personality and rights of citizens), paragraphs &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot; of Part 3 of Article 111 of the Criminal Code (intentional infliction of grievous bodily harm), paragraph &quot;g&quot; of Part 2 of Article 112 of the Criminal Code (intentional infliction of moderate bodily harm). In addition, Vedernikov was found guilty under Part 4 of Article 159 of the Criminal Code (fraud).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The court sentenced Torop and Vedernikov to 12 years in a strict regime colony, and Redkin to 11 years.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The investigation and the court believe that the defendants united into an organized group in 1991 and &quot;with the aim of extracting income from religious activities at the expense of attracting funds from adherents and their labor, as well as from the desire to control people&quot; created a religious association the Church of the Last Testament on the territory of the Krasnoyarsk Territory.&lt;/p&gt;

#Russia #sects

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Pope Leo met with the head and pilgrims of the Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 28, Pope &lt;b&gt;Leo XIV&lt;/b&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vaticannews.va/ru/pope/news/2025-06/papa-palomnikam-ugkc-delites-veroj-posredi-stradanij.html&quot;&gt;met&lt;/a&gt; with pilgrims from the Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church: Supreme Archbishop &lt;b&gt;Sviatoslav Shevchuk&lt;/b&gt;, bishops, priests, monastics, and laity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the Pope, the faithful of the UGCC came from a beautiful land, rich in Christian faith, abundantly watered by the blood of martyrs who, at the cost of their lives, remained faithful to the Apostle Peter and his Successors. He expressed spiritual closeness to long-suffering Ukraine - to children, youth, the elderly, and especially to families mourning their loved ones:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;I share your pain over the captives and victims of this senseless war. I entrust to the Lord your intentions, labors, daily tragedies, and above all - the desire for peace and prosperity.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Pope called on the Greek Catholics to continue the path of church unity, looking to Christ, the source of salvation, and bestowed a blessing on their families, the Church, and the entire Ukrainian people.&lt;/p&gt;

#Ватикан #Catholics #Greek_Catholics

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bishop Seraphim met with Z-politicians in a Bobruisk church&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the City Day in Bobruisk, &quot;honorary&quot; guests from Russia arrived - the head of the Naro-Fominsk urban district &lt;b&gt;Roman Shamne&lt;/b&gt; and the chairman of the Naro-Fominsk urban district Council of Deputies &lt;b&gt;Gennady Penzov&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the Iverskiy Church, they and other guests were met by the Bishop of Bobruisk and Bykhov &lt;b&gt;Seraphim&lt;/b&gt;, as well as the secretary of the Bobruisk diocesan administration, the rector of the Iverskiy Church, Archpriest &lt;b&gt;Sergiy Korovinsky&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The arrivals also visited the Bobruisk Convent of the Holy Myrrh-Bearing Women, where they were met by the abbess of the monastery, Hegumeness &lt;b&gt;Paraskeva (Yelskaya)&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shamne and Penzov are pro-Putin politicians who openly support Russian aggression. Both &lt;a href=&quot;https://nfreg.ru/novosti/roman-shamne-v-ramkah-otchetnoj-kampanii-za-2024-god-provel-ocherednuyu-vstrechu-s-zhitelyami-naro-fominska/&quot;&gt;Roman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://narofominsk.bezformata.com/listnews/naro-fominskogo/147862669/&quot;&gt;Gennady&lt;/a&gt; assist in the delivery of humanitarian aid to the Russian army. The avatar on Roman Shamne&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.instagram.com/p/CacdJkyIu8U/&quot;&gt;Instagram account&lt;/a&gt; has a Z letter with the caption - #WeDoNotAbandonOurOwn.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the opening of the monument to the children of Donbass, Gennady Penzov emphasized:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;There is nothing to talk about, and nothing to discuss. Since the fall of last year, the DPR, LPR, Kherson and Zaporozhye regions are de jure and de facto subjects of the Russian Federation. True, those are the subjects that are currently fighting. Fighting for all of us. For our Slavic, in the broad sense of the word, world.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision&quot;&gt;Christian Vision: NO TO WAR!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;b&gt;&quot;Humanitarian aid has declined&quot;: a military correspondent and Orthodox volunteer from Minsk — on Russian bureaucracy&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Minsk military correspondent and volunteer &lt;b&gt;Nikolai Gavrilov&lt;/b&gt; (in the photo) &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/bch3by/2698&quot;&gt;spoke&lt;/a&gt; about the situation in Donbas, comparing the offensive to a positional fuss, and humanitarian aid to a &quot;mirror world&quot; where a certificate is more important than a drone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to him, assistance to the fighters has &quot;declined significantly&quot;: fraudsters, burnout, but the main thing is the intervention of the state. &quot;Bureaucratically streamline, take under control — registers, special accounts, regulations, certificates with a seal. Everything as we love it — substituting the result with the process,&quot; laments Gavrilov. Against the backdrop of the absence of &quot;Mavics&quot; and bloody battles, this, according to him, looks like an attempt to turn away from reality.&lt;/p&gt;

#belarus #orthodox

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Moscow pastor Nikolai Romanyuk recognized as a political prisoner by human rights defenders&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Russian human rights defenders &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/pzk_memorial/6854&quot;&gt;announced&lt;/a&gt; that the senior pastor of the Pentecostal Church of the Holy Trinity, &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://shaltnotkill.info/romanyuk_ru/&quot;&gt;Nikolai Romanyuk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;, is a political prisoner.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Recall that he is being persecuted for an anti-war sermon delivered in September 2022 in a church in the Moscow region. In it, he called on believers not to participate in hostilities, calling the war a temptation and a sin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The security forces detained Romanyuk with demonstrative cruelty, and his children were laid face down in the courtyard of the house for 12 hours. For more than eight months, the pastor has been in a pre-trial detention center, despite his poor health. His trial will begin in July, and he faces up to 6 years in prison.&lt;/p&gt;

