&lt;p&gt;One of the main ideas of the film is the so-called &quot;triad of Elder Ilya&quot;, a famous archimandrite who died in March of this year. This triad was taken up by &lt;b&gt;Boris Korchevnikov&lt;/b&gt;, the general director of &quot;Spas&quot;, who stated that for Russia to win, three conditions must be met: ban abortions, remove profanity, and remove Lenin&#x27;s body from the mausoleum.&lt;/p&gt;

