&lt;b&gt;Prilepkin attacked the Russian Orthodox Church for wanting to bury Lenin: &quot;Russia will crack like a watermelon&quot;&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Russian left-wing propagandist, a supporter of the war against Ukraine, writer Zakhar Prilepkin criticized the Russian Orthodox Church for wanting to bury the body of Vladimir Lenin. According to him, this is pushing Russia &quot;towards a new civil war&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;People who pass themselves off as Russians (most often the initiators of this outrage are not quite Russian even ethnically, as in Ukraine), who pass themselves off as patriots, who pass themselves off as Orthodox, who pass themselves off as anyone - they are sharpening the very foundations of Russian civilization,&quot; he said.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to him, &quot;in the wake of Lenin, they will inevitably come here for Stalin, for Brezhnev, for the entire Soviet legacy, for Soviet art, for Soviet cinema, for Yesenin&#x27;s poem &#x27;Captain of the Earth&#x27;, for Mayakovsky, for Mukhina, for Vuchetich, for the Soviet song, for the red star and the red flag, which they are not ashamed to call the &#x27;satanic rag&#x27; already now&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prilepkin believes that after that they will come &quot;for the concept of Russian justice&quot;, &quot;shouting about &#x27;purification&#x27; and &#x27;repentance&#x27;&quot;, they will cancel national autonomies &quot;(falsely assuring that they were &#x27;invented by Lenin&#x27;) - and Russia will crack like a watermelon&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

