&lt;p&gt;On The Insider Live, Ksenia Luchenko presented her book &quot;With Good Intentions&quot;, in which she traces the path of the Russian Orthodox Church from the Perestroika era to the Putin era. In a conversation with Nikolai Alexandrov, she called the ROC &quot;de facto the ideological committee&quot; of the current government.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to Luchenko, in the post-Soviet period, the Church was &quot;recreated&quot; from the remnants of the Soviet project and since then has become increasingly intertwined with the state. The book contains 16 essays - stories from neophytes to church officials, from monasteries to nuclear energy - to show how the Church has become an institution of state propaganda.&lt;/p&gt;

