&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The wife of a ROSHVE pastor received a Putin grant to support the wives of occupiers&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The program of comprehensive support for the wives of participants in the aggression against Ukraine &quot;Za Lyubov&quot; (For Love), which is being implemented by the &quot;Star and Lyre&quot; Foundation and the public movement &quot;Being a Mom&quot;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cef.ru/infoblock/news/read/article/1843623&quot;&gt;received&lt;/a&gt; a grant from the President of the Russian Federation in the amount of 3 million rubles.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The program is aimed at comprehensive support for pregnant women and young mothers from the families of participants in the war against Ukraine. The project is timed to coincide with the Year of the Family and the Year of the Defender of the Fatherland.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&quot;The victory in the competition is a recognition of the importance of our work. We are grateful for the trust and intend to do everything to ensure that the women and families of the participants in the special military operation receive the necessary support,&quot;&lt;/i&gt; noted the head of the organization &quot;Being a Mom&quot; &lt;b&gt;Alena Shkurko,&lt;/b&gt; who is also the wife of the plenipotentiary representative of ROSHVE(p) in Samara and the Samara region.&lt;/p&gt;

