&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bishop blessed the concert of Z-artist Oleg Gazmanov in Polotsk&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The event, which took place in one of the oldest centers of Orthodoxy in Belarus - Polotsk, became part of the &quot;Songs of Victory. Voices of Generations&quot; project. It was organized by the autonomous non-profit organization &quot;Gazmanov-Rodniki Movement&quot;. It is headed by the artist &lt;b&gt;Oleg Gazmanov&lt;/b&gt;, who actively supports the Russian aggression against Ukraine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The concert tour started on Poklonnaya Hill in Moscow, after which it took place in several cities of Russia. The event in Polotsk was held with the blessing of the Bishop of Polotsk and Glubokoe &lt;b&gt;Ignatius&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Among the guests were the bishop&#x27;s mother, nun &lt;b&gt;Solomonia (Lukovich)&lt;/b&gt;, the deputy chairman of the Polotsk district executive committee for social issues &lt;b&gt;Svetlana Valyushkina&lt;/b&gt;, the general producer of &quot;Gazmanov-Rodniki&quot; &lt;b&gt;Elena Ulyanova&lt;/b&gt;, and the chairman of the Russian international public organization &quot;Strategy of Unity&quot; &lt;b&gt;Irina Tropina&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bishop Ignatius addressed the audience from the stage:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Our President Alexander Grigorievich says that we have two states, but one Fatherland. I would like this love for the Fatherland, expressed in words, poems and songs, to sound from this stage today. And we together with you would rejoice in communication and that we can exist together under a peaceful sky.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The general producer of &quot;Gazmanov-Rodniki&quot; &lt;b&gt;Elena Ulyanova&lt;/b&gt; thanked for the warm welcome:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Hello, Belarus! Hello, Polotsk! For the first time, the &#x27;Rodniki&#x27; will perform on your land. Thanks to His Grace Ignatius, the Bishop of Polotsk and Glubokoe, we are here today, on your sacred land.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;During the event, Bishop Ignatius presented Rodion Gazmanov, the son of Oleg Gazmanov, with the book &quot;And there will be no cramped in my heart&quot;, published on the occasion of the 100th anniversary of the repose of St. Tikhon, Patriarch of Moscow and All Russia.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Military songs were performed on stage: &quot;Our Tenth Airborne Battalion&quot;, &quot;Front-Line Artists&quot;, &quot;Katyusha&quot; and others.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision&quot;&gt;Christian Vision: NO TO WAR!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;A Russian missile disrupted a Christian children&#x27;s camp in Dnipro&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 24, on the very first day of the summer Christian camp at the &quot;Ark&quot; church in Dnipro, four powerful explosions thundered nearby - the last missile fell very close. More than 100 children aged 7 to 14 in panic &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.christianpost.com/news/russian-missile-disrupts-ukrainian-church-summer-camp.html&quot;&gt;descended&lt;/a&gt; into the church basement, designed for only 50 people. Some were crying, calling for their mothers, others were praying or just staring at one point. There was no connection, the children could not call their parents.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The pastor prayed with them and hugged those who were trembling with fear. After 40 minutes, everyone was taken out into the fresh air. About 50 children with their parents left the camp, but the next day everyone who had to leave returned to the camp, and even brought friends. Despite the trauma, the program continued.&lt;/p&gt;

