&lt;p&gt;On April 30, 2025, Samoylova personally met with Vladimir Putin in Moscow, who praised her, reminding that &quot;the Soviet Union helped fight Nazism in Spain, where the Spanish people fought against the coming to power of the fascist dictatorship.&quot; And this despite the fact that Samoylova is connected with Spanish fascists. Her lawyer, Juan Antonio Aguilar, was on the electoral lists of Spanish fascist parties from 1979 to 2004 and for several years headed the political movement MSR, whose faction was the neo-Nazi group &quot;Blood &amp; Honor&quot;, convicted of illegal possession of weapons.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 2021, Aguilar published the book &quot;We Are What We Defend,&quot; in which he tried to adapt the pro-Nazi concept to the current time, relying on the theses of the philosopher Ivan Ilyin and the &quot;Russian thinker&quot; Alexander Dugin.&lt;/p&gt;

