&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Muslims in Russia remembered international norms and condemned external acts of aggression&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Spiritual Administration of Muslims of the Russian Federation, which supports Russia&#x27;s aggression against Ukraine, continues to sympathize with Iran. The Deputy Chairman of the Spiritual Administration of Muslims of the Russian Federation, Mufti &lt;b&gt;Ruslan Abbasyov&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://dumrf.ru/common/event/25266&quot;&gt;visited&lt;/a&gt; the Embassy of Iran in Moscow, where on behalf of the Chairman, Chief Mufti &lt;b&gt;Ravil Gainutdin&lt;/b&gt; and the Muslim Ummah of Russia, he expressed condolences &lt;i&gt;&quot;in connection with the death of innocent people as a result of external aggression&quot;&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the entry in the Book of Condolences and in a conversation with Iranian Ambassador &lt;b&gt;Kazem Jalali&lt;/b&gt;, Ruslan Abbasyov noted that &lt;i&gt;&quot;Russian Muslims resolutely condemn acts of aggression that have led to the death of Iranian citizens and grossly violate all international norms and humanistic principles&quot;.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The aggression of the Russian Federation against Ukraine, which grossly violates all international norms and humanistic principles, as well as the death of innocent Ukrainians as a result of external aggression, does not cause any objections in the Spiritual Administration of Muslims of the Russian Federation.&lt;/p&gt;

