&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;For donations to the Ukrainian spiritual center, an additional punishment was imposed on a convict from Izhevsk&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have already &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill/10057&quot;&gt;reported&lt;/a&gt; on the 25-year-old resident of Izhevsk &lt;b&gt;Dinara Akhmetova&lt;/b&gt;, convicted for transfers to Ukrainian organizations &lt;b&gt;Vladimir Muntyan&lt;/b&gt;, recognized in the Russian Federation as &quot;undesirable&quot;. In April, she received 240 hours of community service under Article 284.1 of the Criminal Code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now it became known that on the appeal of the prosecutor&#x27;s office, the Supreme Court of Udmurtia &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/sudUdm/2489&quot;&gt;supplemented the sentence&lt;/a&gt;: her phone, from which the transfers were made, was confiscated in favor of the state. The court also credited the time of her detention in custody towards the assigned punishment.&lt;/p&gt;

